quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,127,"And they denied him, so indeed, they will be brought [for punishment],"
  37,128,"Except the chosen servants of Allāh."
  37,129,"And We left for him [favorable mention] among later generations:"
  40,70,"Those who deny the Book [i.e., the Qur’ān] and that with which We sent Our messengers - they are going to know,"
  40,71,"When the shackles are around their necks and the chains; they will be dragged"
  40,72,"In boiling water; then in the Fire they will be filled [with flame]."
  41,49,"Man is not weary of supplication for good [things], but if evil touches him, he is hopeless and despairing."
  41,50,"And if We let him taste mercy from Us after an adversity which has touched him, he will surely say, ",footnotes:1:[Because of my effort, knowledge, excellence, etc.]
  41,51,"And when We bestow favor upon man, he turns away and distances himself; but when evil touches him, then he is full of extensive supplication."
  42,34,"Or He could destroy them{1} for what they earned; but He pardons much.",footnotes:1:[Meaning that Allāh could sink the ships by means of violent winds.]
  42,35,"And [that is so] those who dispute concerning Our signs may know that for them there is no place of escape."
  42,36,"So whatever thing you have been given - it is but [for] enjoyment of the worldly life. But what is with Allāh is better and more lasting for those who have believed and upon their Lord rely"
  43,16,"Or has He taken, out of what He has created, daughters and chosen you for [having] sons?"
  43,17,"And when one of them is given good tidings of that which he attributes to the Most Merciful in comparison [i.e., a daughter], his face becomes dark, and he suppresses grief."
  43,18,"So is one brought up in ornaments while being during conflict unevident{1} [attributed to Allāh]?",footnotes:1:[Not "obvious" or "distinct" in an argument.  Or not "seen," i.e., absent from battles.  The reference is to a daughter.]
  44,1,"Ḥā, Meem.{1}",footnotes:1:[See footnote to 2:1.]
  44,2,"By the clear Book,"
  44,3,"Indeed, We sent it down during a blessed night.{1} Indeed, We were to warn [mankind].",footnotes:1:[The Night of Decree (Qadr).  See sūrah 97.]
